creator: Esri
descriptionHtml: ArcGIS QuickCapture is the simplest way to capture field observations. Record GIS data with a single tap on your device. Automatically send locations, photos, and other attributes back to your office in real time. It’s integrated with ArcGIS, you can effectively visualize data you’ve never had access to before.
descriptionShort: ArcGIS QuickCapture is Esri’s mobile app for at-speed data capture

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
- Improved launch and sharing of projects with app links
- Sign in with PKI authentication added
- Change unit setting used by the app
- Support for webhooks added

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
- New device variables have been added, including geometry lengths and areas, coordinate formats, photo location, and direction.
- EXIF metadata is now saved in captured photos.
- Support has been added for link buttons, bigger buttons, and locked groups of buttons.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
- Stability and performance improvements affecting camera, data capture, data upload, and map display.
- App will automatically calculate the magnetic declination for use in device variables and photo EXIF.
- Webhooks now additionally invoked when line and polygon features are submitted.
- Link buttons can now pass the location to a survey geopoint question.
- Photo location can be used to update the geometry of the captured record.
- Free text option added to project user input choice lists.
